   =20
      Financial literacy
   =20
 =20
Not that the traditional channels are always better! I am a long-time skept=
ic of =E2=80=9Cfinancial literacy=E2=80=9D  education, which consists essen=
tially of giving people quizzes about compound interest as a substitute for=
 a decent social safety net. At Axios yesterday Felix Salmon had a very goo=
d column skewering =E2=80=9Cthe financial literacy industrial complex,=E2=
=80=9D and I recommend that you read it. He writes: =E2=80=9CThe main reaso=
n that teens get targeted is they=E2=80=99re a captive audience for financi=
al education campaigns, many of which come with branding from large financi=
al services companies.=E2=80=9DThe purest possible mechanism of =E2=80=9Cfi=
nancial literacy=E2=80=9D is (1) a banker comes to your school, (2) the ban=
ker tells you that to have a good life you need to start depositing money i=
n the bank, (3) your teacher nods approvingly, (4) you believe them and dep=
osit money in the bank and (5) the bank steals it. Here is an incredible an=
ecdote=C2=A0that Salmon quotes from Lauren Willis of Loyola Law School:To t=
each children about the banking system, a U.S. primary school walked its st=
udents to a local bank where each opened a savings account into which each =
deposited $5. Implicit in this activity is the message that the bank is tru=
stworthy. Another bank then acquired that bank and charged all low balance =
accountholders a monthly maintenance fee that wiped out the children=E2=80=
=99s savings. The children may have learned a more important lesson about t=
he financial sector than the school intended.I love this so much. If I stil=
l worked at Goldman Sachs Group Inc. I=E2=80=99d be pitching elementary sch=
ools on teaching financial literacy through over-the-counter derivatives. =
=E2=80=9CThe way to build wealth is to invest in over-the-counter derivativ=
es as soon as possible, kids. Here, have some over-the-counter derivatives,=
 don=E2=80=99t be shy.=E2=80=9D If someone=C2=A0comes to your school to sel=
l you financial products, what kind of edge do you think you have? What kin=
d of edge do you think they have?=C2=A0We  talked on Wednesday about Robinh=
ood Markets Inc.=E2=80=99s plan to go to colleges and sign people up for tr=
ading accounts. We sure did! That is a thing we talked about on Wednesday.
