=E2=80=99t say what Mass Mutual, or Gill, did wrong? The gist of it is:</p>=
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Gill worked as =E2=80=9Cdirector of e=
ducation and wellness=E2=80=9D for a Mass Mutual brand called =E2=80=9CIn G=
ood Company,=E2=80=9D okay.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">He did=
 a lot of posting about GameStop Corp. on Reddit, Twitter and YouTube, beco=
ming a huge celebrity during its January rally. Those posts did not use his=
 real name or mention his Mass Mutual affiliation, though his YouTube video=
s did show his face. =E2=80=9CGill ran rampant on his personal social media=
,=E2=80=9D the consent order says, =E2=80=9Cfrequently and extensively post=
ing regarding generic and specific securities.=E2=80=9D</li>=09<li style=3D=
"margin-bottom: 5px;">He also traded a lot of GameStop stock and options.</=
li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Mass Mutual =E2=80=9Cfailed reasona=
bly to supervise him.=E2=80=9D</li></ol><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Mass M=
utual had policies prohibiting its employees =E2=80=9Cfrom discussing gener=
ic securities and company business on social media,=E2=80=9D and I guess he=
 violated them, but I am just not sure I understand why regulators would ca=
re about that. Did Gill mislead anyone? Was he providing unsuitable financi=
al advice in his capacity as a registered person? Was he =E2=80=9Cmanipulat=
ing the value of GameStop stock,=E2=80=9D as his boss at In Good Company sa=
id in an email quoted by the regulators? I dunno, in a sense, but not I thi=
nk in an illegal sense. He said he liked the stock, and people agreed with =
him, so the stock went up. Seems fine, or fine-ish.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"ma=
rgin: 16px 0;">By the way, surely Keith Gill has done more to teach ordinar=
y people about the financial system than every other =E2=80=9Cfinancial wel=
lness educator=E2=80=9D in the history of the world combined? Like GameStop=
 was=C2=A0very much a teachable moment, in a way that whatever In Good Comp=
any was up to probably was not. (Do <em>you=C2=A0</em>know what In Good Com=
pany was up to?) The guy explained how stock trading works=C2=A0<a href=3D"=
https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/25071678.256555/aHR0cHM6Ly93d=
