om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Issuer-paid ratings</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The way credit ratings work is that a =
company goes to a credit-ratings firm and asks it to rate the company=E2=80=
=99s bonds, and the ratings firm rates the bond, and the issuer pays the fi=
rm for the rating. One standard lesson of the 2008 financial crisis is that=
