om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">15c2-11</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">My Bloomberg Opinion colleague Brian C=
happatta <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/25071678.=
256555/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDkt=
MTYvYS1iaWctYm9uZC1tYXJrZXQtaGVhZGFjaGUtY291cnRlc3ktb2YtdGhlLXNlYw/607f07ce=
ef4b8524a319a23cB321ad63d" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" s=
tyle=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-wid=
th: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgrou=
nd-color: #ccc;"> has a good column</a> on an absolutely bizarre U.S. Secur=
ities and Exchange Commission rule change. Basically there=E2=80=99s a rule=
, Rule 15c2-11, that says that a broker or dealer cannot =E2=80=9Cpublish a=
ny quotation for a security or ...=C2=A0submit any such quotation for publi=
cation, in any quotation medium, unless=E2=80=9D there is a certain amount =
of publicly available information about the issuer (a prospectus, an annual=
 report, etc.), the dealer has reviewed the information, and the=C2=A0deale=
r thinks it is reliable. The rule is clearly and explicitly aimed at the ov=
er-the-counter <em>stock</em> market, that is, the =E2=80=9Cpink sheets=E2=
=80=9D where penny stocks trade when they can=E2=80=99t qualify to list on =
a stock exchange. Brokers and dealers quote those stocks, some of which hav=
e current public information and some of which are for companies that disap=
peared years ago and trade vestigially on the pink sheets. Tons of fraud ha=
ppens in that market, and one way that the SEC tries to prevent that fraud =
is by prohibiting brokers from quoting the fraudier stocks. And last year t=
he SEC updated Rule 15c2-11 to, I don=E2=80=99t know, =E2=80=9Crecognize ad=
vances in communications technologies=E2=80=9D is <a href=3D"https://link.m=
ail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/25071678.256555/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9=
uZXdzL3ByZXNzLXJlbGVhc2UvMjAyMC0yMTI/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB9e5934e8" ite=
mprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #000000; text-d=
ecoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: =
#000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">what the SEC =
said</a>:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CThese retail=
 investor-focused improvements to Rule 15c2-11 are long overdue,=E2=80=9D s=
aid SEC Chairman Jay Clayton. =C2=A0=E2=80=9CThe technological advancements=
 that have taken place since the rule was last amended enable us to require=
 that information in the OTC market be more timely, enabling investors to m=
ake better informed investment decisions, and reducing fraud in these marke=
ts where retail presence is significant and, unfortunately, pump-and-dump a=
nd other frauds are too common.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px =
0;">=E2=80=9CThe amended rule represents another important step in our tire=
less and proactive efforts to protect retail investors from being victimize=
d by microcap fraud,=E2=80=9D said Stephanie Avakian, Director of the Divis=
ion of Enforcement. =E2=80=A6</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Prior to toda=
y=E2=80=99s amendments, certain of the rule=E2=80=99s previous exceptions p=
ermitted broker-dealers to maintain a quoted market for an issuer=E2=80=99s=
 security in perpetuity, in the absence of current and publicly available i=
nformation about the issuer, and even when the issuer no longer exists. =C2=
=A0Recognizing the ease with which information sharing takes place today, t=
he amendments generally prohibit broker-dealers from publishing quotations =
for an issuer=E2=80=99s security when issuer information is not current and=
 publicly available, subject to certain exceptions.</p></blockquote><p styl=
e=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Fine, fine, all seems fine. But technically the rule =
says =E2=80=9Ca security,=E2=80=9D not =E2=80=9Ca penny stock.=E2=80=9D And=
 while the over-the-counter=C2=A0<em>stock=C2=A0</em>market is basically a =
place to fleece retail investors with penny stocks, the over-the-counter=C2=
=A0<em>bond </em>market is just the bond market. If you buy a corporate bon=
d or an asset-backed security, you do it over the counter, based on a deale=
r quote.=C2=A0=E2=80=9CSecurities that trade on the OTC market are primaril=
y owned by retail investors,=E2=80=9D says the SEC release updating Rule 15=
c2-11, which is just not at all true! It is true of=C2=A0<em>stocks=C2=A0</=
em>that trade OTC, but those are small; the bond market is very big, very i=
nstitutional, and very over-the-counter.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">An=
d while some bond issuers (public companies) have the required public infor=
mation, many (some asset-backed security trusts, private companies with bon=
ds) do not. For many bonds the rule will make it more complicated and time-=
consuming and difficult for dealers to quote markets; for other bonds it wi=
ll just make it impossible. And apparently everyone just assumed that the r=
ule did not apply to bonds, but=C2=A0when the SEC updated it last year, som=
eone thought to call them up and say =E2=80=9Cyou don=E2=80=99t mean bonds =
too do you?=E2=80=9D and the SEC was like =E2=80=9Coh sure we do, bonds too=
, why not.=E2=80=9D Oops!=C2=A0Chappatta:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin=
: 16px 0;">There=E2=80=99s one big problem: The rule, which had long been u=
nderstood to safeguard retail investors from penny stocks and other =E2=80=
=9Cpump-and-dump=E2=80=9D schemes, doesn=E2=80=99t explicitly exclude fixed=
-income assets, except for municipal bonds. The Bond Dealers of America, a =
trade association for securities dealers and banks specializing in fixed in=
come, says SEC staff have informally confirmed that the rule applies equall=
y to both equities and debt.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">H=
ere is <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/25071678.25=
6555/aHR0cHM6Ly9kMzFoemxoazZkaTJoNS5jbG91ZGZyb250Lm5ldC8yMDIxMDgwNi9jNi83ZS=
9hYy9jMy83NWRjMmFhNGZjYmIwZGRhZDAyZTU3MWEvU0lGTUEtQkRBX0RyYWZ0X0V4ZW1wdGlvb=
