dGl2ZVVTXzFfLkRPQ1gucGRm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBc67b9dbc" itemprop=3D"Sto=
ryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: n=
one !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bor=
der-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">a joint letter</a> from t=
he Bond Dealers of America and the Securities Industry and Financial Market=
s Association asking the SEC to exempt bonds from the rule. The deadline fo=
r complying with the rule is Sept. 28, and after that maybe no one will be =
allowed to publish bond quotes anymore? Seems weird. =E2=80=9CPeople are wo=
rried about bond market liquidity=E2=80=9D used to be a big theme around he=
re and, uh, banning bond quotes might bring that back.</p><table class=3D"h=
